caption.text:
How to Actually Convert Views into Leads and Sales 👇

1️⃣ CTA

It sounds obvious, but very few businesses actually do this: include strong calls to action (CTA) in the caption or at the end of your videos. 

This is what turns viewers into leads and sales. How often should you post promotional CTAs? At least 30% of your content should have promotional calls to action. 

That way, you “kill two birds with one stone” — you get a good amount of leads without burning out your audience or coming off as too salesy.

2️⃣ Direct Promo or Lead Magnet

You can either promote your paid offers or your free resources. 

When promoting your paid offers, say something like, “If you want to learn more about how me and my team can help you ____ (dream result) — DM/Comment [keyword] now.” 

With direct promo like this, you can expect a conversion rate of around 0.5% to 3% from views to leads.

When you promote a lead magnet (free resources), you can expect way more leads (5%-30% from views to leads), but these won’t necessarily be the hottest ones who are ready to work with you. 

They’re interested in solving a problem, but the urgency may not be there yet. However, with the good follow-up strategy I’ll share next, you can actually generate more sales using this method than with direct promos.

3️⃣ Follow-ups and Sales

Simply getting DMs, comments, or leads through your bio link doesn’t automatically result in sales, even if people express interest in working with you. You need a strong follow-up sequence and a solid sales script to convert them into customers. 

If you haven’t set up ManyChat funnel yet, or you’re unsure what to message and how to turn your viewers into customers, comment MANYCHAT, and I’ll DM you my free training.

caption.text:
I’ve been using this strategy for 3 years👇

Are you a busy entrepreneur who needs daily content ideas but don’t have time for complex social media strategies?

This strategy is perfect for you 👇

It’s called “Recreate Top Performers”

Here’s how it works: 

You start by finding the most viral videos in your niche.

1️⃣ Go to TikTok. 
2️⃣ Type in the search: “____ (your niche) + tips.” 
3️⃣ Click on the 3 dots in the top right corner. 
4️⃣ Set the filters to “Likes Count” and “Last 3 months.”

That’s how you get access to the most recent tending and viral videos + topics + hooks in your niche. 

Why not use Instagram search?

Because Instagram doesn’t offer these search filters, which makes finding what you need take much longer.

The next step is to recreate those top-performing videos, keeping the hook and video style but sharing your own experience on the topic.

Remember, it’s about keeping the same hooks and video styles, but sharing only experience that you own. That’s the difference between recreating and stealing ✌🏻

If you don’t have experience/opinion on the chosen topic, go to the next one.

Want to know how I recreate top performers and get 10mln views on my content a month?

Comment VIRAL, and I’ll DM you my new training on how to research and recreate viral video ideas in your niche—so you can reach non-followers and gain new followers.
